			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> keynote:</span><br><i>The Field of Software Language Engineering</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AnnekeKleppe.html">Anneke Kleppe</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_1">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_1</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagM">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> This keynote frames SLE as an intersection of software engineering, programming languages, and modeling, emphasizing cross-community transfer of techniques.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> It discusses core concerns in designing software languages, including choices around notations and abstractions.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It highlights the role of language workbenches and tool support as a defining part of the SLE field.
</li></ul></li></ul>
